    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Maple Leafs added experience and toughness yesterday, signing the free-agent forwards Gary Roberts and Shayne Corson to multiyear contracts.</p>
        <p>Roberts had 23 goals and 30 assists in 69 games with the Carolina Hurricanes last season. Corson had 8 goals and 20 assists in 70 games with Montreal.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Maple Leafs added experience and toughness yesterday, signing the free-agent forwards Gary Roberts and Shayne Corson to multiyear contracts.</p>
        <p>Roberts had 23 goals and 30 assists in 69 games with the Carolina Hurricanes last season. Corson had 8 goals and 20 assists in 70 games with Montreal.</p>
        <p>''I don't have to fight Tie Domi anymore,'' Corson said, referring to the Leafs' strongman.</p>
        <p>Shayne Corson doesn't have to fight Tie Domi and I don't have to fight Shayne Corson, Roberts said. ''So I think we're all going to get along just fine.''</p>
        <p>PLUS: HOCKEY</p>
      </block>
